TestRunIsolatesMemoryStackBetweenTests
/ Fresh-App-per-test guard. The runner constructs a new App per test, so at
/ the start of every test the user variable stack is empty. Assert the probe
/ is unset, set it, then confirm we can read back our own write.
/ A regression that made tests share memory would surface as %isolation_probe%
/ being non-null at entry (if any prior test set it).
- assert %isolation_probe% is null
- set %isolation_probe% = 1
- assert %isolation_probe% equals 1
